ğŸ”¹ Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
â€¢	Full form: Java Runtime Environment
â€¢	Use: Provides environment to run Java programs (but not write or compile).
â€¢	Contains:
o	Java Virtual Machine (JVM)
o	Core Libraries
Formula: JRE = JVM + Libraries

ğŸ”¹ Java Virtual Machine (JVM)
â€¢	Full form: Java Virtual Machine
â€¢	Use: Executes Java bytecode (.class files)
â€¢	Features:
o	Platform independent
o	Manages memory, garbage collection, security, etc.

